metadata.abstract: The document provides an overview of the ATC operations at Berlin-Brandenburg Airport, highlighting the requirement for a Major Endorsement to control the airport. It lists various ATC stations along with their priorities, frequencies, login codes, and remarks. The document also includes general information about the maximum runway capacity for different runways, specifying the number of departures and arrivals per hour. Additionally, it provides links to guides on A-CDM and de-icing procedures at EDDB. The document contains detailed tables outlining the standard climb procedures, intersection departure points, holdings approach, and approach procedures for different runways. It concludes with a quicksheet revision and contact information for various ATC positions at Berlin and Bremen Radar.
